<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,324,1403,1429]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[189,1398,1449,1511]" pageId="10" pageNumber="11">This species is named after the character Minerva McGonagall, from the Harry Potter series of books written by the British J.K. Rowling. The name is employed as a noun in apposition.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
