<paragraph blockId="12.[189,1399,526,728]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">
The most similar species to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lima &amp; Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2020" authorityName="Lima &amp; Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2020" box="[534,771,526,552]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cuspidariidae" genus="Cardiomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minerva" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[534,771,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cardiomya minerva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[782,876,527,553]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are 
<taxonomicName authority="van Regteren Altena, 1971" authorityName="van Regteren Altena" authorityYear="1971" class="Bivalvia" family="Cuspidariidae" genus="Cardiomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="surinamensis">
<emphasis box="[933,1229,526,552]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cardiomya surinamensis</emphasis>
van Regteren Altena, 1971
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[362,432,561,588]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,473,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[193,1394,473,1809]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. A–F. Cardiomya minerva sp. nov., holotype (IBUFRJ 5785). A–B. External view, left and right valve. C–D. Details of the posterior radial ribs and the rostrum. E–F. Hinge detail. — G–H. Cardiomya surinamensis van Regteren Altena, 1971, holotype (RMNH.MOL.55387), left valve. G. External view. H. Hinge detail. — I–J. Cardiomya cadiziana Huber, 2010, syntype (USNM 172032), left valve. I. External view. J. Hinge detail. Scale bars: A–B, G–J = 1 mm; C–D = 0.25 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3777251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3777251/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
G–H) and 
<taxonomicName authority="Huber, 2010" authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2010" box="[563,976,562,588]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cuspidariidae" genus="Cardiomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cadiziana">
<emphasis box="[563,818,562,588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cardiomya cadiziana</emphasis>
Huber, 2010
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[995,1066,561,588]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="11.[189,232,1855,1881]" captionTargetBox="[193,1394,473,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[193,1394,473,1809]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Fig. 5. A–F. Cardiomya minerva sp. nov., holotype (IBUFRJ 5785). A–B. External view, left and right valve. C–D. Details of the posterior radial ribs and the rostrum. E–F. Hinge detail. — G–H. Cardiomya surinamensis van Regteren Altena, 1971, holotype (RMNH.MOL.55387), left valve. G. External view. H. Hinge detail. — I–J. Cardiomya cadiziana Huber, 2010, syntype (USNM 172032), left valve. I. External view. J. Hinge detail. Scale bars: A–B, G–J = 1 mm; C–D = 0.25 mm; E–F = 0.5 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3777251" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3777251/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
I–J). These two species can be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Lima &amp; Oliveira &amp; Absalão, 2020" authorityName="Lima &amp; Oliveira &amp; Absalão" authorityYear="2020" box="[458,694,597,623]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cuspidariidae" genus="Cardiomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minerva" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[458,694,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">Cardiomya minerva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[704,797,597,623]" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by their trapezoidal shell flank, external sculpture composed of incomplete radial ribs on anterior region of the shell flank. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Huber" authorityYear="2010" box="[1246,1398,632,659]" class="Bivalvia" family="Cuspidariidae" genus="Cardiomya" kingdom="Animalia" order="Anomalodesmata" pageId="12" pageNumber="13" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cadiziana">
<emphasis box="[1246,1266,633,659]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1284,1398,632,658]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="13">cadiziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
exhibits a shorter rostrum, with several faint radial lines, and straight posterodorsal margin, not extending above the umbones.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
